// PTYManager
// Creates and manages PTY (pseudo-terminal) sessions backed by Bun's native terminal API.
// Each session runs a shell process, buffers its output, and fans output out to
// any number of attached WebSockets.

Sessions are stored in an in-memory Map keyed by session ID. There is no persistence
across server restarts. A single exported singleton (ptyManager) is used throughout
the server. Sessions clean themselves up when the shell process exits.

Output is held in a RingBuffer per session so late-connecting or reconnecting clients
can receive a replay. Replay can be deferred until the client sends its first resize
event (deferReplay mode), which prevents rendering artifacts when the terminal
dimensions aren't yet known.

FUNCTION constructor()                                                  EXPORT
  Initialize an empty sessions Map.

---

FUNCTION getShell(requestedShell) -> string
  CALLS: RingBuffer (RingBuffer)
  IF a specific shell path is requested, verify it exists on disk and return it.
  ELSE use the $SHELL environment variable if it exists on disk.
  ELSE try the fallback chain: /bin/zsh, /bin/bash, /bin/sh — return the first found.
  If none found, throw.

---

FUNCTION create(sessionId, options) -> PTYSessionInfo                   EXPORT
  CALLS: RingBuffer (RingBuffer)
  Reject if a session with this ID already exists, or if the ID is blank.
  Resolve the shell via getShell, cwd, cols (default 80), rows (default 24).
  Build a skeleton session object, then spawn the shell process with Bun's terminal API.
  Register two terminal callbacks — data and exit — described below.
  Attach a backup exit handler on proc.exited to remove the session if the PTY
  callback didn't already do so.
  Store the session and return its public info (id, shell, cwd, timestamps, client count).

---

FUNCTION dataCallback(terminal, data)
  Decode the raw bytes to a string and write to the session's RingBuffer.
  Update lastActivity.
  For each attached WebSocket: send an "output" message, but only if the session has
  already received its first resize OR deferReplay is false. Ignore send errors
  (the WebSocket may already be closed).

---

FUNCTION exitCallback(terminal, exitCode, signal)
  Update lastActivity. Broadcast an "exit" message with the exit code to all WebSockets.
  Remove the session from the Map.

---

FUNCTION write(sessionId, data)                                         EXPORT
  Look up the session; throw if not found.
  Write the data string directly to the terminal. Update lastActivity.

---

FUNCTION resize(sessionId, cols, rows)                                  EXPORT
  Look up the session; return silently if not found.
  Resize the terminal. Track whether this is the first resize received.
  IF it was the first resize and deferReplay is active and WebSockets are connected,
  call replayBuffer for each connected WebSocket.
  Update lastActivity.

---

FUNCTION attach(sessionId, ws, options)                                 EXPORT
  CALLS: RingBuffer (RingBuffer)
  Look up the session. IF it doesn't exist, auto-create one using the same spawn logic
  as create (same data/exit callbacks, same defaults). Store the new session.
  Add the WebSocket to the session's set.
  Store the deferReplay flag and reset hasReceivedResize to false.
  IF NOT deferring, immediately send the full buffer contents to this WebSocket as an
  "output" message.
  Update lastActivity.

---

FUNCTION replayBuffer(sessionId, ws)                                    EXPORT
  Look up the session; return silently if not found.
  Send the full buffer contents to the given WebSocket as an "output" message.

---

FUNCTION detach(sessionId, ws)                                          EXPORT
  Remove the WebSocket from the session's set. The shell process keeps running.

---

FUNCTION kill(sessionId)                                                EXPORT
  Look up the session; return silently if not found.
  Broadcast an "exit" message with code -1 to all WebSockets, then close each one.
  Close the terminal and kill the process.
  Clear the buffer and remove the session from the Map.

---

FUNCTION list() -> PTYSessionInfo[]                                     EXPORT
  Return public info for every active session.

---

FUNCTION has(sessionId) -> boolean                                      EXPORT
  Return whether a session with this ID exists.

---

FUNCTION get(sessionId) -> PTYSessionInfo | undefined                   EXPORT
  Return public info for the session, or undefined if not found.

---

FUNCTION killAll()                                                      EXPORT
  Call kill on every session. Used during server shutdown.

---

ptyManager                                                              EXPORT
  Singleton PTYManager instance created at module load time.
